SUMMARIZER="A">   

A coalition of members of Congress plans to sue the Census Bureau to
prevent it from including illegal immigrants in its 1990 census
count. The suit to be filed by some 40 members of Congress and the
Federation for American Immigration Reform contends that including 2
million or more illegal aliens in the count would cause unfair shifts
of seats from one state to another when reapportionment takes
place. Census officials counter that the U.S. Constitution calls for
apportionment to be based on the "whole number of persons" residing in
the various states and makes no mention of citizenship in this
regard.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d19"
TYPE="PERDOC"
SIZE="100"
DOCREF="AP880330-0119"
SELECTOR="D"
SUMMARIZER="A"> 

While there is pressure on the Census Bureau to exclude illegal aliens
from its national head count, other groups urge the Bureau to adjust
its final figures to account for people missed in the census--mostly
minorities in urban areas. A population expert with the Population
Reference Bureau says that deleting the illegal aliens and adding an
estimate of the uncounted would result in a loss of one seat for
California and a gain of one seat for Georgia. The expert also
predicted that Northeast and Midwest states will lose 14 House seats
following the 1990 census, continuing a trend observed for several
decades.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d19"
TYPE="PERDOC"
SIZE="100"
DOCREF="AP880623-0135"
SELECTOR="D"
SUMMARIZER="A"> 

There was vigorous debate in the House Census Subcommittee Thursday
over whether illegal aliens should be counted in the 1990 census. On
the one side it was argued that states with large numbers of illegal
aliens benefit unfairly getting extra house seats as a result of
having residents who have violated the law while the rights of honest
citizens in other states are violated as they lose representation in
the House. On the other side it was pointed out that the Constitution
requires a count of all the "persons" in the country for purposes of
reapportionment and does not specify citizens.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d19"
TYPE="PERDOC"
